Brews Brother LLC<br>
Job Description<br>
<br>
Job Title:	Cook<br>
Department:	Kitchen<br>
Reports to:	Kitchen supervisor/Sous-chef/Executive Chef<br>
<br>
<br>
SUMMARY<br>
Prepares, seasons, and cooks soups, Rotisserie meats, seafood, pasta, vegetables, and desserts, to order (ala carte kitchen) or in bulk (prep kitchen & bakery).<br>
<br>
ESSENTIAL DUTIES AND RESPONSIBILITIES include the following.  Other duties may be assigned.<br>
Able to follow all training guidelines and completes all quizzes.<br>
Reads menu and preference reports to estimate and maintain pa level requirements for smooth restaurant operation.<br>
Operates oven, broilers, grills, rotisserie, steamer, gas burners, slicer, knives and mixers.<br>
Measures and mixes ingredients according to recipe.<br>
Ability to prepare and plate multiple items according to recipe.<br>
Observes and tests foods being cooked by tasting, smelling, and using a food thermometer.<br>
Washes, peels, cuts, and shreds vegetables and fruits to prepare them for use.<br>
Cuts meats, chickens, fish and shellfish.<br>
Bakes bread, rolls, cakes and pastries.<br>
Follows all haccp, food preparation and sanitation guidelines applicable to the job.<br>
Sweeps, mops and cleans work stations as applicable.<br>
Maintains a clean, pressed, proper fitting uniform.<br>
<br>
QUALIFICATIONS:  To perform this job successfully, an individual must be able to perform each essential duty satisfactorily, and to have reasoning ability and basic math skills.  The requirements listed below are representative of the knowledge, skill, and /or ability required.  Reasonable accommodations may be made to enable individuals with disabilities to perform the essential functions.<br>
<br>
EDUCATION and/or EXPERIENCE<br>
Culinary degree or certificate or equal industry experience.<br>
<br>
PHYSICAL DEMANDS  The physical demands described here are representative of those that must be met by an employee to successfully perform the essential functions of this job.  Reasonable accommodations may be made to enable individuals with disabilities to perform the essential functions.<br>
<br>
Able to stand for extended period of time, (6-9 hours).<br>
Able to correctly lift 60 lbs.<br>
Able to correctly lift loads exceeding 60 lbs with assistance.<br>
Able to deal with stressful situations or encounters.<br>
Able to make repetitive slicing and cutting motion.<br>
<br>
<br>
<br>
WORK ENVIRONMENT  The work environment characteristics described here are representative of those an employee encounters while performing the essential functions of this job.  Reasonable accommodations may be made to enable individuals with disabilities to perform the essential functions.<br>
<br>
Hot humid environments with temperatures which may exceed 90 degrees during peak summer volume.<br>
Able to work in walk-in refrigerators/freezers for short periods of time.<br>
Able to work on wet/slippery surfaces.<br>
Able to work around wood fires.<br>
    </section>

